PUNCT_TO_REMOVE = string.punctuation
def remove_punctuation(text):
    """custom function to remove the punctuation"""
    return text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', PUNCT_TO_REMOVE))

df["text_wo_punct"] = df["text_lower"].apply(lambda text: remove_punctuation(text))

    """custom function to remove the stopwords"""
    return " ".join([word for word in str(text).split() if word not in STOPWORDS])

from wordcloud import WordCloud
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def show_wordcloud(data, title = None):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(
        background_color = 'white',
        max_words = 200,
        max_font_size = 40, 
        scale = 3,
        random_state = 42
    ).generate(str(data))

    fig = plt.figure(1, figsize = (20, 20))
    plt.axis('off')
    if title: 
        fig.suptitle(title, fontsize = 20)
        fig.subplots_adjust(top = 2.3)

    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.show()
    
# print wordcloud
show_wordcloud(df["text_wo_stop"])

from nltk.corpus import wordnet
from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer

lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
wordnet_map = {"N":wordnet.NOUN, "V":wordnet.VERB, "J":wordnet.ADJ, "R":wordnet.ADV}
def lemmatize_words(text):
    pos_tagged_text = nltk.pos_tag(text.split())
    return " ".join([lemmatizer.lemmatize(word, wordnet_map.get(pos[0], wordnet.NOUN)) for word, pos in pos_tagged_text])

df["text_lemmatized"] = df["text_stemmed"].apply(lambda text: lemmatize_words(text))

def remove_emoji(string):
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', string)

df["remove_emoji"] = df["text_lemmatized"].apply(lambda text: remove_emoji(text))

def remove_emoticons(text):
    emoticon_pattern = re.compile(u'(' + u'|'.join(k for k in EMOTICONS) + u')')
    return emoticon_pattern.sub(r'', text)

df["remove_emoticons"] = df["remove_emoji"].apply(lambda text: remove_emoticons(text))
In [0]:
def convert_emoticons(text):
    for emot in EMOTICONS:
        text = re.sub(u'('+emot+')', "_".join(EMOTICONS[emot].replace(",","").split()), text)
    return text

df["convert_emoticons"] = df["remove_emoticons"].apply(lambda text: convert_emoticons(text))
In [0]:
def remove_urls(text):
    url_pattern = re.compile(r'https?://\S+|www\.\S+')
    return url_pattern.sub(r'', text)

df["remove_urls"] = df["remove_emoticons"].apply(lambda text: convert_emoticons(text))

def remove_html(text):
    html_pattern = re.compile('<.*?>')
    return html_pattern.sub(r'', text)

# Creating function for calculating positive, negative and neutral
# More than 1 --> Positive, equal to 0 --> neutral and less than 0 --> Negative
def ratio(x):
 if x > 0:
  return 1
 elif x == 0:
  return 0
 else:
  return -1
